        "original_url": "https://merveilles.town/@akkartik/110069492107710107",
        "fallback": "Merveilles: Kartik Agaram (@akkartik@merveilles.town)",
        "text": "Srini Kadamati: \"On January 1, Apple sunsetted the Dark Sky app (acquired in 2020) and integrated it into the Apple Weather app.\n\n\"But Dark Sky was much more than a set of “forecast technologies.” The design of the Dark Sky mobile application was a hallmark of information design.\"\n\n<https://nightingaledvs.com/dark-sky-weather-data-viz>\n\nMe: \"Companies that don’t grow revenues get acquired by companies that do.\"\n\n<https://lobste.rs/s/nzsunh/meanwhile_over_androidtown#c_saohr6>\n\nUX is too often temporary. To make it permanent, focus on the DX. Open source and more.",
        "title": "Kartik Agaram (@akkartik@merveilles.town)",
        "title_link": "https://merveilles.town/@akkartik/110069492107710107",
        "service_name": "Merveilles"
