    "client_msg_id": "ccaeafb5-c53e-41bb-9d4c-3e36dc61210d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Really, you haven't ever found Google or Facebook or Twitter or Apple to seem abusive?\n\nI think it's reasonable to say personal relationships are different from relationships with companies. We don't make ourselves as vulnerable with companies, so it makes no sense to call anything abuse.\n\nIt also seems fertile to think of them as akin to personal relationships (hence my &lt;3 above). But then it seems to me you do have to admit the full spectrum of emotions a relationship can engender.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1679605852.568369",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "/=6n",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Really, you haven't ever found Google or Facebook or Twitter or Apple to seem abusive?\n\nI think it's reasonable to say personal relationships are different from relationships with companies. We don't make ourselves as vulnerable with companies, so it makes no sense to call anything abuse.\n\nIt also seems fertile to think of them as akin to personal relationships (hence my <3 above). But then it seems to me you do have to admit the full spectrum of emotions a relationship can engender."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
