    "type": "message",
    "text": "yeah <@UCUSW7WVD> FWIW I had to pay $4 or $5 for the app :slightly_smiling_face: but clearly wasnt’ enough revenue. People just don’t really pay for weather apps unfortunately.\n\nI think Apple actually noticed that there were lots of free weather apps doing sketchy things from a user privacy standpoint + stuffed with ads, b/c again historically people didn’t pay for a weather app. They may have bought Dark Sky to power WeatherKit, and make it easier for other people to build weather apps. So interesting roller coaster overall",
